     1	# SDK Live Smoke
     2	
     3	This smoke is an autonomous, no-human-input harness for proving the SDK against a live Keeper tenant through Commander CLI 17.x, while honoring the current "no DAG writes" moratorium by routing all tenant mutations through Commander rather than direct `keeper_dag` writes. Both the `deploy_watcher` helper path and the public `EnvLoginHelper` path are wired into the same plan -> apply -> verify -> destroy harness; Issue #3 is live-proven for the full `pamMachine` cycle.
     4	
     5	The `pamRemoteBrowser` and `pamUserNestedRotation` scenarios are proof harnesses, not support claims for Issues #5 and #4. A 2026-04-25 `pamRemoteBrowser` live run created records and cleanup passed, but verification failed because Commander `pam rbi edit --remote-browser-isolation` writes DAG `allowedSettings.connections`, which current `discover()` does not read back as manifest-shaped `pam_settings.options.remote_browser_isolation`. Nested rotation now reaches apply and marker verification after `pam rotation edit`, but the follow-up plan still reports updates for the nested user and parent machine; keep the preview/experimental gates until readback/drift semantics are clean. **Pre-merge contract:** `docs/SDK_DA_COMPLETION_PLAN.md` § Phase 0 — do not lift preview gates without parent-reviewed live proof per that plan.
     6	
     7	## Prerequisites
     8	
     9	- Keeper Commander >= 17.2.13 on PATH (`keeper --version`)
    10	- `pip` packages installed: `keepercommander`, `pyotp`, `keeper_secrets_manager_core`, `pyyaml`
    11	- Admin KSM config at `../keeper-vault-rbi-pam-testenv/ksm-config.json`
    12	- Admin commander config at `../keeper-vault-rbi-pam-testenv/commander-config.json` with a valid `device_token` (persistent login)
    13	- Admin has already stored admin-KSM record `MyiZN4cw-wtEIpY1jHlhLw` ("Admin Creds for Lab Scripts" or similar) containing the admin login, password, and `oneTimeCode`
    14	- Tenant contains the gateway `Lab GW Rocky` bound to PAM configuration `Lab Rocky PAM Configuration`
    15	- `testuser2` (`msawczyn+testuser2@acme-demo.com`) exists and is active
    16	
    17	## Files
    18	
    19	| file | purpose | public functions |
    20	|------|---------|------------------|
    21	| `identity.py` | Bootstraps the live identities: admin login via KSM-backed lab helpers, plus idempotent `testuser2` TOTP provisioning and Commander config reuse. | `admin_login()`, `ensure_sdktest_identity()`, `sdktest_keeper_args()`, `main()` |
    22	| `sandbox.py` | Ensures the reusable shared-folder sandbox and KSM app exist, are shared correctly, and can tear down only SDK-managed records. | `ensure_sandbox()`, `record_count()`, `teardown_records()`, `teardown_sandbox()`, `main()` |
    23	| `scenarios.py` | Registry of resource shapes the smoke can exercise. Each `ScenarioSpec` supplies a manifest fragment builder and a post-apply verifier; the runner is resource-type-agnostic. | `get()`, `names()`, `all_scenarios()` |
    24	| `smoke.py` | Orchestrates the live end-to-end smoke: pre-clean, manifest generation, validate/plan/apply, live verification, destroy, and failure cleanup. Scenario-aware via `--scenario`. | `run_smoke()`, `main()` |
    25	
    26	## One-command run
    27	
    28	Single scenario:
    29	
    30	```bash
    31	python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py                          # pamMachine (default)
    32	python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --scenario pamDatabase   # Postgres cycle
    33	python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --scenario pamDirectory  # OpenLDAP cycle
    34	python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --scenario pamRemoteBrowser
    35	python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --scenario pamUserNested # machine + nested users[]
    36	python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --login-helper env --scenario pamMachine
    37	python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --login-helper env --scenario pamRemoteBrowser # Issue #5 proof; currently expected to expose RBI readback gap
    38	DSK_PREVIEW=1 DSK_EXPERIMENTAL_ROTATION_APPLY=1 python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --login-helper env --scenario pamUserNestedRotation
    39	```
    40	
    41	Operator-side sequential or parallel matrix runners live in the
    42	maintainer's private daybook (`msawczynk/cursor-daybook`:
    43	`templates/agent/`); this repo only ships the per-scenario CLI.
    44	
    45	Registered scenarios live in `scripts/smoke/scenarios.py`. Every scenario
    46	is unit-tested offline (`tests/test_smoke_scenarios.py`) — schema,
    47	typed-model, planner, and Commander JSON normalization all run without
    48	a tenant, so scenario drift is caught before you burn a tenant
    49	round-trip.
    50	
    51	| scenario | status | note |
    52	|----------|--------|------|
    53	| `pamMachine` | supported | Default two-host Linux machine cycle. |
    54	| `pamDatabase` | supported | Postgres cycle. |
    55	| `pamDirectory` | supported | OpenLDAP cycle. |
    56	| `pamRemoteBrowser` | experimental proof | Issue #5 RBI readback gap remains. |
