     1	# Live-proof artifacts (`docs/live-proof/`)
     2	
     3	**Audience:** maintainer, **Cursor orchestrator**, **Codex CLI**, or any other
     4	agent / CI **explicitly granted** live access to a lab tenant for this repo
     5	(same bar as [`AGENTS.md`](../AGENTS.md) § Autonomous execution). Read this
     6	before changing `x-keeper-live-proof.status` on a family schema.
     7	
     8	**Normative rules:** `keeper_sdk/core/schemas/CONVENTIONS.md` (block shape,
     9	`since_pin` = full 40-char SHA from `.commander-pin`). Meta schema:
    10	`keeper_sdk/core/schemas/_meta/x-keeper-live-proof.schema.json`.
    11	
    12	**Vault L1 semantics (before interpreting a vault transcript):** [`VAULT_L1_DESIGN.md`](../VAULT_L1_DESIGN.md) §4 and [`VALIDATION_STAGES.md`](../VALIDATION_STAGES.md) (*Vault — operator caveats*) — scalar diff limits, races, offline vs `vault_online` CI.
    13	
    14	**Prerequisite health:** the **orchestrator** keeps smoke/L1 prerequisites
    15	aligned with `scripts/smoke/README.md` and records pass/fail in the daybook —
    16	same ownership as `AGENTS.md` § Autonomous execution.
    17	
    18	## Live access for code (agents, workers, CI, Codex)
    19	
    20	Live proof is **not** parent-only. The orchestrator, **Codex CLI**, workers, or
    21	CI may hold the L1 gate **when**:
    22	
    23	- The maintainer has granted **standing or per-sprint** permission (see
    24	  `AGENTS.md` — smoke harness, **Codex/orchestrator** runs with the same
    25	  whitelist, or a task body that lists exact argv / scenarios and tenant scope).
    26	- The actor uses **committed** harnesses or documented CLI steps — not
    27	  exploratory shell on the tenant.
    28	- Raw capture stays **out of git** until sanitized; the same rules as
    29	  `dsk report` / `secret_leak_check` apply to anything that lands in the repo.
    30	
    31	**Concurrency:** one writer per profile per tenant, when profiles use disjoint
    32	Commander config paths, test users, shared folders, KSM apps, and project
    33	names. The smoke harness enforces this via per-profile lock files when
    34	`--parallel-profile` is set; without `--parallel-profile`, the legacy
    35	single-writer-per-tenant rule still applies.
    36	
    37	## Naming convention (committed files only)
    38	
    39	After sanitization, prefer:
    40	
    41	```text
    42	docs/live-proof/<family>.v<major>.<commander-pin-abbrev>.sanitized.json
    43	```
    44	
    45	Example: `keeper-vault.v1.89047920.sanitized.json` (use the first 7–8 hex
    46	chars of the pin for humans; `since_pin` in the schema stays **full 40**).
    47	
    48	Use `.sanitized.` in the basename so reviewers grep for it in PRs.
    49	
    50	## What “sanitized” means
    51	
    52	Nothing in the committed artifact may recover:
    53	
    54	- Passwords, TOTP seeds, PEM / private keys, session tokens, or config blobs
    55	- Values of `KEEPER_PASSWORD`, `KEEPER_TOTP_SECRET`, or similar env echoes
    56	
    57	Use the same discipline as `dsk report` / `secret_leak_check` and the live
    58	transcript helpers (`keeper_sdk.cli._live.transcript`). When in doubt, keep
    59	**structure and lengths** (e.g. `"password": "<redacted>"`) not literal secrets.
    60	
    61	## L1 execution checklist (human or granted automation)
    62	
    63	1. **Branch** off current `main`; note `.commander-pin` SHA (full 40) in the
    64	   sprint log.
    65	2. **Run** the smallest scenario that exercises the schema family (see
    66	   `scripts/smoke/README.md` when a scenario exists; otherwise a one-off
    67	   `dsk plan` / `dsk validate --online` path documented in the PR).
    68	3. **Capture** stdout/stderr to a scratch file **outside** the repo (or in
    69	   `.gitignore`); never push raw.
    70	4. **Redact** into the naming pattern above; run `python3 -m json.tool` on JSON
    71	   artifacts before commit (strict RFC 8259).
    72	5. **Grep** the artifact for `BEGIN`, `PRIVATE`, long base64 runs, and any lab
    73	   hostname/email you used — fix until clean.
    74	6. **Commit** artifact + update the family schema:
    75	   - `x-keeper-live-proof.status` → `supported` (or `preview-gated` if gated by
    76	     `DSK_PREVIEW=1` per SDK_DA).
    77	   - `x-keeper-live-proof.evidence` → repo-relative path to this directory.
    78	   - `since_pin` → exact `.commander-pin` line.
    79	7. **Open PR** with a one-line “clean re-plan” or equivalent proof statement in
    80	   the description (SDK_DA completion gates).
    81	
    82	## V8 prep (not live evidence)
    83	
    84	**Template JSON (shape only):** [`keeper-vault.v1.sanitized.template.json`](./keeper-vault.v1.sanitized.template.json) — `template: true`; safe to commit. After a tenant run, produce a real `*.sanitized.json` per the naming rule above, redact, then point `x-keeper-live-proof.evidence` at that file.
    85	
    86	**Sample manifest (one `login`):** [`../examples/scaffold_only/vaultOneLogin.yaml`](../examples/scaffold_only/vaultOneLogin.yaml) — edit `uid_ref` / title / field values for your lab folder; keep non-production credentials only.
    87	
    88	## Current placeholders
    89	
    90	| Family | Schema status | Evidence pointer |
    91	|--------|---------------|------------------|
    92	| `keeper-vault.v1` | `scaffold-only` | Commander L1 + `validate --online` in code; commit a **sanitized** transcript (see template + checklist §6) before `supported` |
    93	| `keeper-vault-sharing.v1` | `scaffold-only` | This README until a transcript lands |
    94	| `keeper-enterprise.v1` | `scaffold-only` | This README until a transcript lands |
    95	
    96	When a real file exists, point `evidence` at that file path instead of this
    97	README.
    98	
    99	## Parallel orchestration
   100	
   101	See `docs/NEXT_SPRINT_PARALLEL_ORCHESTRATION.md` — **R4** is the prep that feeds
   102	**L1** (one writer per profile per tenant when `--parallel-profile` enforces
   103	disjoint profile locks; otherwise serial per tenant) then **F3** (schema
   104	pointer + artifact commit).

