    29	```
    30	# GH Actions parallel smoke matrix — design memo (CDX-S4, <UTC ISO>)
    31	
    32	## Trigger
    33	- Nightly cron `0 4 * * *` UTC.
    34	- Manual `workflow_dispatch` for ad-hoc runs.
    35	
    36	## Job structure
    37	- One job: `smoke-matrix` (in addition to existing `build` job; depends on it).
    38	- Matrix dimensions:
    39	  - `profile`: [p1, p2, p3]
    40	  - `scenario`: [pamMachine, pamDatabase, pamDirectory, pamRemoteBrowser, pamUserNested]  (pamUserNestedRotation excluded — preview-gated)
    41	- `fail-fast: false` so one failure doesn't kill the rest.
    42	- Concurrency group: `smoke-matrix-${{ github.workflow }}` with `cancel-in-progress: true` to prevent overlapping cron runs.
    43	
    44	## Per-job steps
    45	1. Checkout (full).
    46	2. Set up Python 3.11.
    47	3. Install: `pip install -e ".[dev]" keepercommander pyotp keeper_secrets_manager_core`.
    48	4. Materialise per-profile JSON file from secrets:
    49	   - Each profile reads `secrets.SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_<UPPER>_JSON`. (Operator provisions these as a JSON blob each.)
    50	   - Write to `scripts/smoke/profiles/<profile>.json`.
    51	   - Materialise per-profile Commander config from `secrets.SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_<UPPER>` to the path declared in the profile JSON.
    52	5. Materialise admin KSM config once: `secrets.SDK_SMOKE_KSM_CONFIG`.
    53	6. Provision testuser identity: `python3 scripts/smoke/identity.py --profile <profile>`.
    54	7. Run smoke: `python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --profile <profile> --scenario <scenario> --login-helper env --parallel-profile`.
    55	8. Upload artifact: smoke log + sanitized post-mortem JSON, retention 14 days.
    56	9. On failure: emit grouped log section + last 200 lines of smoke output.
    57	
    58	## Required secrets (operator provisions ONCE)
    59	- `SDK_SMOKE_KSM_CONFIG`: full ksm-config.json blob.
    60	- `SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_P1_JSON`, `..._P2_JSON`, `..._P3_JSON`: per-profile config blob.
    61	- `SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_P1`, `..._P2`, `..._P3`: per-profile admin commander-config.json blob (each pointing at the same admin user but with isolated cache DB paths).
    62	- (Already exists for any current secret-needing job — confirm names by reading `ci.yml`.)
    63	
    64	## Cost estimate
    65	- 3 × 5 = 15 jobs/night.
    66	- ~3min per job (per current `scripts/smoke/README.md` smoke run time estimates).
    67	- Total: ~45min compute/night. Free for public repo on GH Actions.
    68	
    69	## Concurrency safety
    70	- All 15 jobs run on different runners — no cross-job process collision.
    71	- Within tenant: profile lock files prevent two jobs from grabbing the same profile simultaneously (S3 deliverable). Matrix `fail-fast: false` + `cancel-in-progress: true` on the workflow keeps the lock window bounded.
    72	
    73	## Reporting
    74	- After matrix completes, a summary job aggregates results into a single GitHub Actions Job Summary (Markdown table).
    75	- Optional: post a comment to a tracking issue (`#1` or new "nightly smoke" issue).
    76	
    77	## Risk + rollback
    78	- Risk 1: tenant rate limit. Mitigation: cap matrix concurrency to 5 (`max-parallel: 5`) so only 5 of the 15 cells run at once. Operator can raise after first stable week.
    79	- Risk 2: profile lock collision if two scenarios land on same profile in the same run (impossible with current matrix shape, but defended by lock file).
    80	- Risk 3: secrets accidentally logged. Mitigation: `actions/setup-python@v5` masking + `set-output` only on sanitized values; smoke log already redacts via `secret_leak_check`.
    81	- Rollback: delete the workflow file; matrix is additive and does not change existing CI.
    82	
    83	## Live-proof artifact capture
    84	- Each successful nightly auto-commits a sanitized transcript artifact to `docs/live-proof/auto/<date>-<profile>-<scenario>.sanitized.json` IF status changed (e.g. flake → green or vice versa). This is OUT OF SCOPE for the first matrix landing — file as Sprint 7h-39+ follow-up.
    85	
