   162	
   163	The service runs `keeper enterprise-role <ROLE_ID> --add-user <email>` and `--remove-user` after the timer, using **`KEEPER_CLI`** (default `keeper`). The process must run as the **same Windows user** (or same POSIX account) that completed Commander login, so the existing device session is used. If `keeper` only works in interactive mode on your build, adjust to the documented batch invocation for your OS or keep `COMMANDER_DRY_RUN=true` for testing.
