# Operator-Bootstrap Playbook: L2 + L4

## Section 1: Why This Is Operator-Only

L2 needs live tenant identities and per-profile Commander/KSM material that a readonly worker must not invent: each non-default profile is loaded from `scripts/smoke/profiles/<id>.json`, and real JSON files are gitignored (`scripts/smoke/identity.py:102-119`, `scripts/smoke/profiles/.gitignore:1-2`). L4 needs GitHub repo secrets containing those profile JSON blobs, per-profile Commander configs, and the KSM config; the S4 memo explicitly leaves those as operator-provisioned secrets (`docs/sprint-memos/7h-37-S4-ci-matrix.codex.log:48-62`, `docs/sprint-memos/7h-37-S4-ci-matrix.codex.log:3634-3639`).

## Section 2: L2 Prerequisites

Use disjoint config directories, not flat `~/.keeper/p1.json`, because Commander creates `keeper_db.sqlite` beside each config file (`/Users/martin/Library/Python/3.14/lib/python/site-packages/keepercommander/params.py:350-358`). Raw Commander honors `--config` and `KEEPER_CONFIG_FILE` (`/Users/martin/Library/Python/3.14/lib/python/site-packages/keepercommander/__main__.py:40-54`, `/Users/martin/Library/Python/3.14/lib/python/site-packages/keepercommander/__main__.py:120-153`).

```bash
export DSK_KSM_CONFIG="$HOME/.keeper/dsk-smoke/admin-ksm-config.json"
mkdir -p "$HOME/.keeper/dsk-smoke"/p{1,2,3}/{admin,sdktest}
```

For each `N=1 2 3`, create the tenant user. Commander’s installed enterprise parser uses `enterprise-user --add` for invite and `create-user` for reserved-domain auto-provision (`/Users/martin/Library/Python/3.14/lib/python/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/enterprise.py:152-177`, `/Users/martin/Library/Python/3.14/lib/python/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/enterprise_create_user.py:37-43`). Lab tenant docs live at `../keeper-vault-rbi-pam-testenv/README.md` and point provisioning to `scripts/provision_manual.md` (`../keeper-vault-rbi-pam-testenv/README.md:127-130`, `../keeper-vault-rbi-pam-testenv/scripts/provision_manual.md:23-30`).

```bash
N=1
EMAIL="msawczyn+sdk-p${N}@acme-demo.com"
ADMIN_CFG="$HOME/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p${N}/admin/config.json"

keeper --config "$ADMIN_CFG" login <TENANT_ADMIN_EMAIL>
keeper --config "$ADMIN_CFG" --batch-mode enterprise-user --add --name "SDK Smoke p${N}" "$EMAIL"
# If the tenant uses reserved-domain auto-provision and you need a known generated password:
keeper --config "$ADMIN_CFG" --batch-mode create-user --name "SDK Smoke p${N}" "$EMAIL"
```

Record the actual test-user password in the matching profile JSON. `ensure_sdktest_identity()` later clears 2FA, logs in as the profile user with `profile.password`, enrolls TOTP, and writes the profile test-user Commander config (`scripts/smoke/identity.py:524-548`, `scripts/smoke/identity.py:590-631`).

Provision disjoint smoke resources. Non-default profiles use `SDK Test (ephemeral) <id>`, `SDK Test KSM <id>`, and `sdk-smoke-<id>` while sharing gateway `Lab GW Rocky` (`scripts/smoke/sandbox.py:41-49`, `scripts/smoke/identity.py:46-59`).

```bash
SF_TITLE="SDK Test (ephemeral) p${N}"
KSM_APP="SDK Test KSM p${N}"
PROJECT="sdk-smoke-p${N}"

keeper --config "$ADMIN_CFG" --batch-mode mkdir -sf --manage-users --manage-records --can-edit --can-share "$SF_TITLE"
keeper --config "$ADMIN_CFG" --batch-mode share-folder "$SF_TITLE" -a grant -e "$EMAIL" -p on -o on -d on -s on -f
keeper --config "$ADMIN_CFG" --batch-mode secrets-manager app create "$KSM_APP"
SF_UID="$(keeper --config "$ADMIN_CFG" --batch-mode ls -f --format json | jq -r ".[] | select(.name==\"$SF_TITLE\") | .uid")"
keeper --config "$ADMIN_CFG" --batch-mode secrets-manager share add --app "$KSM_APP" --secret "$SF_UID" --editable
keeper --config "$ADMIN_CFG" --batch-mode rmdir -f "PAM Environments/$PROJECT" || true
```

Drop `scripts/smoke/profiles/p<N>.json`. The required fields come from `_REQUIRED_PROFILE_FIELDS` and the example schema (`scripts/smoke/identity.py:90-99`, `scripts/smoke/profiles/default.example.json:1-12`). Use `~` paths so the same JSON works locally and on GitHub runners; `_profile_path()` expands `~` (`scripts/smoke/identity.py:144-148`).

```json
{
  "id": "p1",
  "target_email": "msawczyn+sdk-p1@acme-demo.com",
  "ksm_config": "~/.keeper/dsk-smoke/admin-ksm-config.json",
  "admin_commander_config": "~/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p1/admin/config.json",
  "sdktest_commander_config": "~/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p1/sdktest/config.json",
  "keeper_server": "keepersecurity.com",
  "channel_name": "sdk-declarative-p1",
  "password": "<KNOWN_TEST_USER_PASSWORD>",
  "default_admin_record_uid": "<ADMIN_CREDS_RECORD_UID>",
  "sdk_test_login_record_title": "SDK Test — sdk-p1 Login"
}
```

Repeat for `p2` and `p3`, changing every `p1`/`sdk-p1`/path segment to `p2` or `p3`.

Validate each profile:

```bash
python3 -c "from scripts.smoke.identity import load_profile; print(load_profile('p1'))"
python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --scenario pamMachine --profile p1
python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --scenario pamMachine --profile p2
python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --scenario pamMachine --profile p3
```

Validate parallel guard acceptance for disjoint lanes. The lock directory defaults to `<repo>/.dsk-smoke-locks`, with files named `.dsk-smoke-<tenant>-<profile>.lock` (`scripts/smoke/parallel_guard.py:45-50`, `scripts/smoke/parallel_guard.py:161-164`; README summary at `scripts/smoke/README.md:184-187`).

```bash
python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --scenario pamMachine --profile p1 --parallel-profile &
python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --scenario pamMachine --profile p2 --parallel-profile &
wait
```

## Section 3: L4 Prerequisites

The S4 memo requires profile JSON secrets, per-profile Commander config secrets, and one KSM config secret (`docs/sprint-memos/7h-37-S4-ci-matrix.codex.log:58-62`, `docs/sprint-memos/7h-37-S4-ci-matrix.codex.log:3720-3725`). Current smoke uses the KSM-backed deploy_watcher path for admin creds, and even `--login-helper env` re-fetches admin creds from that helper (`scripts/smoke/identity.py:494-510`, `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:301-315`, `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:687-700`).

```bash
gh secret set SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_P1_JSON < scripts/smoke/profiles/p1.json
gh secret set SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_P2_JSON < scripts/smoke/profiles/p2.json
gh secret set SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_P3_JSON < scripts/smoke/profiles/p3.json

base64 < "$HOME/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p1/admin/config.json" | tr -d '\n' | gh secret set SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_P1
base64 < "$HOME/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p2/admin/config.json" | tr -d '\n' | gh secret set SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_P2
base64 < "$HOME/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p3/admin/config.json" | tr -d '\n' | gh secret set SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_P3

gh secret set SDK_SMOKE_KSM_CONFIG < "$DSK_KSM_CONFIG"
```

Validate secrets:

```bash
gh secret list | grep -E 'SDK_SMOKE_(PROFILE_P[123]_JSON|COMMANDER_CONFIG_P[123]|KSM_CONFIG)'
```

Expected names: `SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_P1_JSON`, `SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_P2_JSON`, `SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_P3_JSON`, `SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_P1`, `SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_P2`, `SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_P3`, `SDK_SMOKE_KSM_CONFIG`.

After L4 lands the matrix workflow, trigger a single profile and then the full matrix. The design memo names the job `smoke-matrix` and the axes `profile: [p1,p2,p3]` plus supported scenarios excluding rotation (`docs/sprint-memos/7h-37-S4-ci-matrix.codex.log:36-54`, `docs/sprint-memos/7h-37-S4-ci-matrix.codex.log:3602-3612`).

```bash
gh workflow run smoke-matrix.yml -f profile=p1
gh run watch --exit-status

gh workflow run smoke-matrix.yml
gh run watch --exit-status
```

Expect three profile lanes in parallel, with same-profile scenario cells queued by workflow or lock policy (`docs/live-proof/README.md:31-35`, `docs/sprint-memos/7h-37-S4-ci-matrix.codex.log:3641-3647`).

## Section 4: Common Pitfalls

1. Commander config rewrite-in-place: back up configs before testing. The SDK provider passes `--config <path>` to Commander (`keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:1657-1660`), and Commander writes config back to `params.config_filename` (`/Users/martin/Library/Python/3.14/lib/python/site-packages/keepercommander/config_storage/loader.py:118-123`).

```bash
for N in 1 2 3; do
  cp "$HOME/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p${N}/admin/config.json" "$HOME/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p${N}/admin/config.json.bak.$(date -u +%Y%m%dT%H%M%SZ)"
done
```

2. Cache DB collision: do not put all configs in `~/.keeper/p<N>.json` for parallel runs, because the cache DB is created beside the config filename (`/Users/martin/Library/Python/3.14/lib/python/site-packages/keepercommander/params.py:350-358`). Use profile-specific directories and keep those exact paths in profile JSON (`scripts/smoke/identity.py:133-140`).

3. KSM marker version skew: core marker version is `1` (`keeper_sdk/core/metadata.py:27-29`), and diff raises `OwnershipError` when a managed record has an unsupported marker version (`keeper_sdk/core/diff.py:464-470`). Recover by deleting only SDK-managed smoke records and recreating the project, not by hand-editing markers:

```bash
python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --teardown --profile p1
keeper --config "$HOME/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p1/admin/config.json" --batch-mode rmdir -f "PAM Environments/sdk-smoke-p1"
```

4. Parallel guard refusal: `--parallel-profile` refuses the default profile (`scripts/smoke/parallel_guard.py:78-80`), the default lab config (`scripts/smoke/parallel_guard.py:82-88`), `KEEPER_CONFIG` mismatches (`scripts/smoke/parallel_guard.py:90-96`), active admin-config collisions (`scripts/smoke/parallel_guard.py:103-112`), and active shared-folder/KSM-app/project collisions on the same tenant (`scripts/smoke/parallel_guard.py:113-120`). Fix the profile JSON path or resource names, then re-run.

5. Stuck locks: dead-PID locks are auto-removed, but a live PID older than 24h refuses until the operator verifies no smoke is active (`scripts/smoke/parallel_guard.py:58-68`, `scripts/smoke/README.md:189-192`).

## Section 5: Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] All 3 profile JSONs exist at `scripts/smoke/profiles/p<N>.json`.
- [ ] All 3 admin Commander configs exist at documented disjoint paths such as `~/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p<N>/admin/config.json`.
- [ ] Sequential single-profile `pamMachine` smoke passed for `p1`, `p2`, and `p3`.
- [ ] Parallel-profile guard accepted a disjoint pair, at least `p1+p2`.
- [ ] All 7 GitHub Actions secrets are registered and the smoke matrix workflow is GREEN.

When this checklist is pasted back checked, the orchestrator can fire L2 and L4 in one fan-out.

