## Section 3: L4 Prerequisites

The S4 memo requires profile JSON secrets, per-profile Commander config secrets, and one KSM config secret (`docs/sprint-memos/7h-37-S4-ci-matrix.codex.log:58-62`, `docs/sprint-memos/7h-37-S4-ci-matrix.codex.log:3720-3725`). Current smoke uses the KSM-backed deploy_watcher path for admin creds, and even `--login-helper env` re-fetches admin creds from that helper (`scripts/smoke/identity.py:494-510`, `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:301-315`, `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:687-700`).

```bash
gh secret set SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_P1_JSON < scripts/smoke/profiles/p1.json
gh secret set SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_P2_JSON < scripts/smoke/profiles/p2.json
gh secret set SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_P3_JSON < scripts/smoke/profiles/p3.json

base64 < "$HOME/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p1/admin/config.json" | tr -d '\n' | gh secret set SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_P1
base64 < "$HOME/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p2/admin/config.json" | tr -d '\n' | gh secret set SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_P2
base64 < "$HOME/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p3/admin/config.json" | tr -d '\n' | gh secret set SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_P3

gh secret set SDK_SMOKE_KSM_CONFIG < "$DSK_KSM_CONFIG"
```

Validate secrets:

```bash
gh secret list | grep -E 'SDK_SMOKE_(PROFILE_P[123]_JSON|COMMANDER_CONFIG_P[123]|KSM_CONFIG)'
```

Expected names: `SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_P1_JSON`, `SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_P2_JSON`, `SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_P3_JSON`, `SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_P1`, `SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_P2`, `SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_P3`, `SDK_SMOKE_KSM_CONFIG`.

After L4 lands the matrix workflow, trigger a single profile and then the full matrix. The design memo names the job `smoke-matrix` and the axes `profile: [p1,p2,p3]` plus supported scenarios excluding rotation (`docs/sprint-memos/7h-37-S4-ci-matrix.codex.log:36-54`, `docs/sprint-memos/7h-37-S4-ci-matrix.codex.log:3602-3612`).

```bash
gh workflow run smoke-matrix.yml -f profile=p1
gh run watch --exit-status

gh workflow run smoke-matrix.yml
gh run watch --exit-status
```

Expect three profile lanes in parallel, with same-profile scenario cells queued by workflow or lock policy (`docs/live-proof/README.md:31-35`, `docs/sprint-memos/7h-37-S4-ci-matrix.codex.log:3641-3647`).

## Section 4: Common Pitfalls

1. Commander config rewrite-in-place: back up configs before testing. The SDK provider passes `--config <path>` to Commander (`keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:1657-1660`), and Commander writes config back to `params.config_filename` (`/Users/martin/Library/Python/3.14/lib/python/site-packages/keepercommander/config_storage/loader.py:118-123`).

```bash
for N in 1 2 3; do
  cp "$HOME/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p${N}/admin/config.json" "$HOME/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p${N}/admin/config.json.bak.$(date -u +%Y%m%dT%H%M%SZ)"
done
```

2. Cache DB collision: do not put all configs in `~/.keeper/p<N>.json` for parallel runs, because the cache DB is created beside the config filename (`/Users/martin/Library/Python/3.14/lib/python/site-packages/keepercommander/params.py:350-358`). Use profile-specific directories and keep those exact paths in profile JSON (`scripts/smoke/identity.py:133-140`).

3. KSM marker version skew: core marker version is `1` (`keeper_sdk/core/metadata.py:27-29`), and diff raises `OwnershipError` when a managed record has an unsupported marker version (`keeper_sdk/core/diff.py:464-470`). Recover by deleting only SDK-managed smoke records and recreating the project, not by hand-editing markers:

```bash
python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --teardown --profile p1
keeper --config "$HOME/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p1/admin/config.json" --batch-mode rmdir -f "PAM Environments/sdk-smoke-p1"
```

4. Parallel guard refusal: `--parallel-profile` refuses the default profile (`scripts/smoke/parallel_guard.py:78-80`), the default lab config (`scripts/smoke/parallel_guard.py:82-88`), `KEEPER_CONFIG` mismatches (`scripts/smoke/parallel_guard.py:90-96`), active admin-config collisions (`scripts/smoke/parallel_guard.py:103-112`), and active shared-folder/KSM-app/project collisions on the same tenant (`scripts/smoke/parallel_guard.py:113-120`). Fix the profile JSON path or resource names, then re-run.

5. Stuck locks: dead-PID locks are auto-removed, but a live PID older than 24h refuses until the operator verifies no smoke is active (`scripts/smoke/parallel_guard.py:58-68`, `scripts/smoke/README.md:189-192`).

## Section 5: Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] All 3 profile JSONs exist at `scripts/smoke/profiles/p<N>.json`.
- [ ] All 3 admin Commander configs exist at documented disjoint paths such as `~/.keeper/dsk-smoke/p<N>/admin/config.json`.
- [ ] Sequential single-profile `pamMachine` smoke passed for `p1`, `p2`, and `p3`.
- [ ] Parallel-profile guard accepted a disjoint pair, at least `p1+p2`.
- [ ] All 7 GitHub Actions secrets are registered and the smoke matrix workflow is GREEN.

When this checklist is pasted back checked, the orchestrator can fire L2 and L4 in one fan-out.

